headline: France’s Government Softens Plan to Raise Employer Taxes
summary: (Bloomberg) -- France’s government plans to reduce the scale of proposed tax increases for employers as it seeks to preserve pro-business policies while also plugging holes in public finances, budget minister Laurent Saint-Martin said.
